(24, 'Recenzii de Gadget-uri &amp; Software', 'FÄƒrÄƒ urmÄƒ de &icirc;ndoialÄƒ, lansÄƒrile de la &icirc;nceput de an ale noilor flagship-uri din gamele Galaxy S sunt cele mai importante pentru Samsung, dict&acirc;nd inclusiv modul &icirc;n care celelalte produse ale companiei vor fi percepute &icirc;n restul anului. Iar dintre acestea, este logic ca producÄƒtorul sud-coreean sa se concentreze, &icirc;n primul r&acirc;nd, pe v&acirc;rful de gamÄƒ &ndash; acum Galaxy S25 Ultra &ndash;, perceput drept &bdquo;best of the best&rdquo; &icirc;n privinÈ›a a ce are Samsung de oferit &icirc;n 2025. SÄƒ nu uitam cÄƒ predecesorul acestui telefon &ndash; Galaxy S24 Ultra &ndash; a fost un dispozitiv extrem de bine conceput, care a excelat &icirc;n 2024 la mai toate capitolele, afl&acirc;ndu-se pe listele de recomandÄƒri ale tuturor publicaÈ›iilor de profil. AÈ™adar, ce te faci c&acirc;nd propriul tÄƒu smartphone de anul trecut reprezintÄƒ unul dintre principalii concurenÈ›i ai modelului tÄƒu flagship de anul acesta?\r\n\r\nConstrucÈ›ie È™i design. Avantaj S25 Ultra\r\nAminteam mai devreme cÄƒ Galaxy S24 Ultra a excelat la mai toate capitolele, una dintre excepÈ›ii fiind design-ul sau greoi È™i colÈ›uros. Aici a adus Samsung poate cele mai &bdquo;palbabile&rdquo; &icirc;mbunÄƒtÄƒÈ›iri modelului S25 Ultra, elimin&acirc;nd colÈ›urile ascuÈ›ite, incomode mai ales atunci c&acirc;nd &icirc;ncercai sÄƒ È›ii telefonul &icirc;ntr-un buzunar mai str&acirc;mt, È™i &icirc;nlocuindu-le cu cele rotunjite, design-ul devenind aproape identic cu cel al modelelor S25 È™i S25 Plus (sau S24 È™i S24 Plus, dacÄƒ vreÈ›i).\r\n\r\nAstfel, poate cÄƒ Galaxy S25 Ultra pierde un pic din propria identitate vizualÄƒ (&icirc;n comparaÈ›ie cu S24 Ultra), &icirc;nsÄƒ c&acirc;È™tigÄƒ foarte mult &icirc;n ceea ce priveÈ™te factorul ergonomic. AdÄƒugaÈ›i È™i construcÈ›ia de calitate &icirc;naltÄƒ, cu ecran plat È™i cadru metalic din titan, dar È™i greutatea mai micÄƒ dec&acirc;t cea a modelului flagship de anul trecut È™i obÈ›ineÈ›i imaginea telefonului aproape perfect &icirc;n ceea ce priveÈ™te uÈ™urinÈ›a È™i comoditate &icirc;n utilizare. &Icirc;n ceea ce priveÈ™te rezistenÈ›a la praf È™i apÄƒ, Samsung poate meritÄƒ sÄƒ fie un pic traÈ™i de urechi: concurenÈ›a a fÄƒcut deja pasul la certificare IP69, &icirc;n timp ce S25 UItra se mulÈ›umeÈ™te &icirc;n continuare cu IP68.\r\n\r\n&Icirc;n schimb, S25 Ultra face pasul la sticla Gorilla Glass Armor 2 pentru protecÈ›ia ecranului, aceasta asigur&acirc;nd, precum o fÄƒcea È™i prima generaÈ›ie de pe S24 Ultra, un strat antireflectiv la care alÈ›i producÄƒtori de telefoane pot doar sÄƒ viseze. Pe de altÄƒ parte, dupÄƒ luni &icirc;ntregi de folosire, stratul oleofob de pe S24 Ultra dÄƒ semne de slÄƒbiciune, ecranul telefonului murdÄƒrindu-se foarte rapid de amprente È™i alte impuritÄƒÈ›i. RÄƒm&acirc;ne de vÄƒzut dacÄƒ È™i protecÈ›ia ecranului, &icirc;n cazul lui S25 Ultra, va &icirc;mbÄƒtr&acirc;ni la fel de repede.\r\n\r\nSpecificaÈ›iile de top nu (mai) reprezintÄƒ un factor decisiv\r\nNu mÄƒ &icirc;nÈ›elegeÈ›i greÈ™it, fiind vorba despre v&acirc;rful ofertei celor de la Samsung &icirc;n ceea ce priveÈ™te smartphone-urile, era logic ca S25 Ultra sÄƒ adopte unul dintre modelele de top de procesoare disponibile pe piaÈ›Äƒ, &bdquo;alesul&rdquo; fiind Snapdragon 8 Elite de la Qualcomm, &icirc;ntr-o ediÈ›ie personalizatÄƒ &bdquo;Made for Galaxy&rdquo;. DeÈ™i &icirc;n cadrul evenimentului de lansare oficialii Samsung insistau cÄƒ nu mai este vorba despre un model supratactat al cipului Qualcomm, se pare cÄƒ adevÄƒrul este altul. Cele douÄƒ nuclee principale ale variantei &bdquo;Made for Galaxy&rdquo; beneficiazÄƒ de frecvenÈ›e de funcÈ›ionare mai ridicate, 4,47 GHz vs. 4,32 GHz, asigur&acirc;nd terminalului Samsung poziÈ›ii fruntaÈ™e &icirc;n mai toate benchmark-urile.\r\n\r\nPe de altÄƒ parte, nu am fost niciodatÄƒ adeptul acestor unelte de benchmarking &bdquo;sterile&rdquo;, care nu fac dec&acirc;t ca telefoanele sÄƒ se rÄƒzboiascÄƒ &icirc;n privinÈ›a unor cifre, cu foarte puÈ›inÄƒ relevanÈ›Äƒ pentru experienÈ›a unui utilizator normal. AdevÄƒrul este cÄƒ Samsung Galaxy S25 Ultra se va comporta &bdquo;ca un campion&rdquo;, indiferent de aplicaÈ›iile sau jocurile pe care i le puneÈ›i &icirc;n faÈ›Äƒ. La fel de adevÄƒrat este ca orice telefon dotat cu un procesor de top c&acirc;t de c&acirc;t recent, inclusiv S24 Ultra cu al sÄƒu Snapdragon 8 Gen 3, se va comporta la fel de bine, &icirc;n sensul &icirc;n care utilizatorul nu va percepe diferenÈ›e notabile &icirc;ntre cele douÄƒ terminale. AceastÄƒ paritate este ajutatÄƒ È™i de cantitatea de memorie RAM identicÄƒ &icirc;ntre cele douÄƒ generaÈ›ii de telefoane, Samsung opt&acirc;nd pentru &bdquo;numai&rdquo; 12 GB de memorie RAM at&acirc;t pentru flagship-ul din 2024, c&acirc;t È™i pentru cel de anul acesta. Din nou, sud-coreenii sunt un pic depÄƒÈ™iÈ›i, concurenÈ›a venind cu modele care pleacÄƒ de la 16 GB de memorie RAM.', '1741014689s25.png', '2025-03-03 15:11:29', 21, 17, 0, 'Gadget and Software Reviews\n\n\n', 'Gadget and Software Reviews\nSamsung Galaxy S25 Ultra â€“ First Impressions\n\nWithout a doubt, the launch of the new Galaxy S flagship phones at the beginning of the year is one of the most important events for Samsung, often dictating how the company\'s other products will be perceived throughout the rest of the year. And among them, itâ€™s only logical that the South Korean manufacturer would focus primarily on the top-tier model â€“ now the Galaxy S25 Ultra â€“ seen as the \"best of the best\" in what Samsung has to offer in 2025.\n\nLetâ€™s not forget that its predecessor, the Galaxy S24 Ultra, was an extremely well-designed device that excelled in almost all areas in 2024, appearing on the recommendation lists of virtually every tech publication.\nSo the question becomes: What do you do when your own previous-year flagship is your new flagship\'s biggest competitor?\n\nBuild and Design: Advantage S25 Ultra\nAs mentioned earlier, the Galaxy S24 Ultra performed exceptionally well in most areas, with design being one of the few exceptions due to its bulky and angular form. This is where Samsung brought perhaps the most noticeable improvement with the S25 Ultra, eliminating the sharp corners â€“ uncomfortable especially when trying to fit the phone in tighter pockets â€“ and replacing them with rounded edges, making the design almost identical to the S25 and S25 Plus (or S24 and S24 Plus, if you prefer).\n\nThus, while the Galaxy S25 Ultra may lose a bit of its distinct visual identity (compared to the S24 Ultra), it gains a lot in terms of ergonomics. Add to that a high-quality build, with a flat display and titanium metal frame, and a lighter weight than last year\'s flagship, and you get a near-perfect phone in terms of ease and comfort of use.\n\nWhen it comes to dust and water resistance, Samsung may deserve a little criticism: competitors have already stepped up to IP69 certification, while the S25 Ultra still sticks with IP68.\n\nOn the flip side, the S25 Ultra upgrades to Gorilla Glass Armor 2 for screen protection, which, like the first generation used on the S24 Ultra, provides an anti-reflective coating that most other manufacturers can only dream of.\nHowever, after months of use, the oleophobic layer on the S24 Ultra shows signs of wear, with the screen quickly smudging with fingerprints and grime. It remains to be seen if the screen protection on the S25 Ultra will age just as quickly.\n\nTop Specs Are No Longer a Decisive Factor\nDonâ€™t get me wrong: being the top-of-the-line model in Samsungâ€™s smartphone lineup, itâ€™s only natural that the S25 Ultra would use one of the most powerful chipsets on the market. The chosen one is Qualcomm\'s Snapdragon 8 Elite, in a customized \"Made for Galaxy\" edition.\n\nAlthough during the launch event Samsung officials claimed itâ€™s no longer just an overclocked version of the Qualcomm chip, it seems the truth is a bit different. The two main cores of the \"Made for Galaxy\" variant do benefit from higher clock speeds â€” 4.47 GHz vs. 4.32 GHz â€” giving Samsungâ€™s flagship top scores in almost every benchmark.\n\nThat said, I\'ve never been a fan of these \"sterile\" benchmark tools, which just pit phones against each other with numbers that have very little relevance to a regular userâ€™s experience.\n\nThe truth is, the Samsung Galaxy S25 Ultra performs like a champion, regardless of what apps or games you throw at it. Equally true is the fact that any recent top-tier processor phone, including the S24 Ultra with its Snapdragon 8 Gen 3, will perform just as well â€” in the sense that the average user wonâ€™t notice any major differences.\n\nThis parity is also helped by the fact that both generations have the same amount of RAM: Samsung opted for \"just\" 12 GB of RAM on both the 2024 and 2025 flagship. Once again, Samsung is slightly behind the competition, which now starts offering devices with 16 GB of RAM or more.'),
(37, 'Kremlinul nu se grÄƒbeÈ™te sÄƒ rÄƒspundÄƒ propunerii de armistiÈ›iu pentru 30 de zile &icirc;n Ucraina: &bdquo;SÄƒ nu ne grÄƒbim&rdquo;', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Secretarul de presÄƒ al preÈ™edintelui rus, Dmitri Peskov, a declarat, miercuri, cÄƒ Moscova &bdquo;analizeazÄƒ atent&rdquo; declaraÈ›iile fÄƒcute dupÄƒ discuÈ›iile dintre SUA È™i Ucraina. Acesta a &icirc;ndemnat la prudenÈ›Äƒ &icirc;n privinÈ›a &icirc;ncetÄƒrii focului de 30 de zile, asupra cÄƒreia Kievul È™i-a exprimat acordul, relateazÄƒ Kommersant È™i agenÈ›ia rusÄƒ de presÄƒ TASS. &bdquo;SÄƒ nu ne grÄƒbim. Ieri, at&acirc;t Rubio, c&acirc;t È™i Waltz au declarat presei cÄƒ ne vor furniza detalii suplimentare despre discuÈ›iile de la Jeddah prin diferite canale diplomatice. Mai &icirc;nt&acirc;i trebuie sÄƒ primim aceste informaÈ›ii. Avem È™i contacte programate cu americanii &icirc;n zilele urmÄƒtoare, &icirc;n cadrul cÄƒrora aÈ™teptÄƒm clarificÄƒri complete&rdquo;, a spus Dmitri Peskov. &Icirc;n urma negocierilor dintre delegaÈ›iile americane È™i ucrainene desfÄƒÈ™urate &icirc;n Arabia SauditÄƒ, Ucraina a acceptat o &icirc;ncetare a focului pentru 30 de zile, cu posibilitatea de prelungire. Potrivit preÈ™edintelui ucrainean Volodimir Zelenski, propunerea Statelor Unite se referÄƒ la un armistiÈ›iu total, &icirc;n aer, pe mare È™i pe uscat. Anterior, liderul de la Kiev a cerut un armistiÈ›iu parÈ›ial, &icirc;n aer È™i pe mare. Washingtonul s-a angajat sÄƒ transmitÄƒ aceastÄƒ propunere Moscovei prin diverse canale diplomatice. PreÈ™edintele american Donald Trump a declarat cÄƒ delegaÈ›ia SUA va avea cur&acirc;nd o &icirc;nt&acirc;lnire cu reprezentanÈ›ii ruÈ™i, iar Ministerul rus de Externe nu a exclus astfel de contacte &icirc;n zilele urmÄƒtoare.<br>CiteÅŸte &icirc;ntreaga ÅŸtire:&nbsp;<a title=\"Kremlinul nu se grÄƒbeÈ™te sÄƒ rÄƒspundÄƒ propunerii de armistiÈ›iu pentru 30 de zile &icirc;n Ucraina: &bdquo;SÄƒ nu ne grÄƒbim&rdquo;\" href=\"https://www.libertatea.ro/stiri/kremlinul-nu-se-grabeste-sa-raspunda-propunere-armistitiu-in-ucraina-5229797\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Kremlinul nu se grÄƒbeÈ™te sÄƒ rÄƒspundÄƒ propunerii de armistiÈ›iu pentru 30 de zile &icirc;n Ucraina: &bdquo;SÄƒ nu ne grÄƒbim&rdquo;</a></p>', '1741776519ukraine.png', '2025-03-12 10:48:39', 25, 12, 1, 'The Kremlin is in no rush to respond to the 30-day ceasefire proposal in Ukraine: â€œLetâ€™s not rushâ€', 'Kremlin not in a hurry to respond to the 30-day ceasefire proposal in Ukraine: â€œLetâ€™s not rushâ€\n\nThe press secretary of the Russian president, Dmitry Peskov, stated on Wednesday that Moscow is â€œclosely analyzingâ€ the statements made following the discussions between the U.S. and Ukraine. He urged caution regarding the proposed 30-day ceasefire, which Kyiv has agreed to, according to Kommersant and the Russian news agency TASS.\n\nâ€œLetâ€™s not rush. Yesterday, both Rubio and Waltz told the press that they would provide us with additional details about the discussions in Jeddah through various diplomatic channels. First, we need to receive that information. We also have scheduled contacts with the Americans in the coming days, during which we expect complete clarifications,â€ said Dmitry Peskov.\n\nFollowing the negotiations between U.S. and Ukrainian delegations held in Saudi Arabia, Ukraine has accepted a 30-day ceasefire, with the possibility of extension. According to Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky, the U.S. proposal refers to a total ceasefire â€” by air, sea, and land. Previously, Kyiv had requested a partial ceasefire (air and sea only).\n\nWashington has committed to passing this proposal on to Moscow through diplomatic channels.\nU.S. President Donald Trump announced that the U.S. delegation will soon meet with Russian representatives, and the Russian Foreign Ministry has not ruled out such contacts in the coming days.\n\nRead the full article: Kremlin not in a hurry to respond to 30-day ceasefire proposal in Ukraine: â€œLetâ€™s not rushâ€ â€“ Libertatea'),
(41, 'Ucraina cere Rusiei sÄƒ returneze peste 500 de copii luaÈ›i din Herson CiteÅŸte &icirc;ntreaga ÅŸtire: Ucraina cere Rusiei sÄƒ returneze peste 500 de copii luaÈ›i din Herson', '<p>Printre aceÈ™tia se numÄƒrÄƒ È™i copii transferaÈ›i din Centrul Regional pentru Copii din Herson &icirc;n Crimeea, &icirc;n toamna anului 2022. O sursÄƒ apropiatÄƒ administraÈ›iei preÈ™edintelui Volodimir Zelenski a declarat cÄƒ lista include circa 400 de copii despre care informaÈ›iile au fost deja transmise unor organizaÈ›ii internaÈ›ionale, dar È™i &bdquo;c&acirc;teva sute&rdquo; de cazuri noi. O altÄƒ sursÄƒ implicatÄƒ &icirc;n investigarea deportÄƒrii minorilor &icirc;n Rusia a afirmat cÄƒ pe listÄƒ s-ar putea afla &bdquo;peste cinci sute de copii&rdquo; ale cÄƒror situaÈ›ii au fost verificate. Printre ei se aflÄƒ aproximativ 50 de copii relocaÈ›i &icirc;n Crimeea ocupatÄƒ, inclusiv la internatul &bdquo;Yolochka&rdquo; din Simferopol. &Icirc;n acest grup se regÄƒsesc È™i Ilia Vascenko È™i Margarita Prokopenko, mutaÈ›i din Herson de soÈ›ia politicianului rus Serghei Mironov &ndash; cazul Margaritei fiind cunoscut dupÄƒ ce a fost adoptatÄƒ. Lista ar mai include copii de la internatul pentru nevoi speciale din OleÈ™ki, &icirc;nchis dupÄƒ ocuparea oraÈ™ului de cÄƒtre trupele ruse. Documentul a fost &icirc;ntocmit prin colaborarea mai multor instituÈ›ii ucrainene: Serviciul de Securitate al Ucrainei (SBU), serviciile de tutelÄƒ, poliÈ›ia È™i Oficiul Avocatului Poporului. &Icirc;nsÄƒ, potrivit sursei, cele mai multe informaÈ›ii vin din anchetele penale derulate de procuraturÄƒ È™i SBU, care pot confirma deportÄƒrile sau traseul minorilor.<br>CiteÅŸte &icirc;ntreaga ÅŸtire:&nbsp;<a title=\"Ucraina cere Rusiei sÄƒ returneze peste 500 de copii luaÈ›i din Herson\" href=\"https://www.libertatea.ro/stiri/ucraina-cere-rusiei-sa-returneze-peste-500-de-copii-luati-din-herson-5330007\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Ucraina cere Rusiei sÄƒ returneze peste 500 de copii luaÈ›i din Herson</a></p>', '1748962291hepta7510713.jpg', '2025-06-03 11:19:34', 25, 12, 0, 'Ukraine asks Russia to return over 500 children taken from Herson Read the full story: Ukraine asks Russia to return over 500 children taken from Herson', '<p>These include children transferred from the Regional Children\'s Center in Herson &icirc;n Crimea in the fall of 2022. A source close to President Volodimir Zelenski\'s administration said the list includes about 400 children about whom information has already been passed on to international organizations, as well as &bdquo;several hundred&rdquo; new cases. Another source involved in investigating the deportation of minors to Russia said the list could include more than 500 children whose situations have been verified. Among them are about 50 children resettled in occupied Crimea, including at the Yolochka boarding school in Simferopol. The group also includes Ilia Vascenko and Margarita Prokopenko, who were moved from Herson by the wife of Russian politician Sergei Mironov, Margarita\'s case became known after she was adopted. The list would also include children from the boarding school for special needs in Oleski, which was closed after Russian troops occupied the town. The document was drafted with the cooperation of several Ukrainian institutions: the Security Service of Ukraine (SBU), guardianship services, police and the People\'s Advocate\'s Office. However, according to the source, most information comes from criminal investigations conducted by the prosecutor\'s office and the SBU, which can confirm the deportations or the route of the minors.<br>Read the full story:&lt;&lt;<a title=\"Ukraine asks Russia to return over 500 children taken from Herson\" href=\"https://www.libertatea.ro/stiri/ucraina-cere-ruraina-cere-rusiei-sa-return-peste-500-de-copii-lauti-lauti-din-herson-5330007\\\" target=\"_blank\\\" rel=\"noopener\\\">Ukraine asks Russia to return over 500 children taken from Herson</a></p>');

